main event: A weatherman stationed at the Mercury Test Site in Nevada observed an unidentified object through a theodolite on June 5, 1961.
interesting points: The object arrived from the south, orbited the area, turned 50 degrees to the west, and disappeared heading west at approximately 1632 Zulu time.
The observer estimated the object's altitude to be between 88,000 and 123,000 feet.
The object held its altitude throughout the sighting, disappearing approximately over Lathrop Wells, Nevada.
The observer utilized the maximum magnification power of the theodolite but was unable to get a fix on the object.
A T-33 aircraft was vectored to the area where the object was last seen, but the aircraft had negative sighting results.
sighted object: one lens-shaped, silver, and hazy object
witnesses: a weatherman stationed at the Mercury Test Site
